explanation: The solution uses a recursive backtracking approach to generate all possible combinations. It first generates all combinations of length 1, then iteratively builds combinations of increasing length by adding characters from the remaining part of the string. The `generate_combinations` function handles the base case (combination length 1) and recursively calls `generate_combinations_recursive` to explore all possible combinations. The `generate_combinations_recursive` function adds a character to the current combination and recursively explores combinations with the remaining characters. The `combinations` list stores all generated combinations.

